          <h3>Lion's Mane</h3>
          <p><em>Hericium erinaceus</em> — <strong>Cognitive Function & Nerve Health.</strong> Stimulates nerve growth factor (NGF) and BDNF production, essential for neuron growth and myelination. Clinical studies show improvements in memory recall and processing speed at 500mg–3,000mg daily over 8–16 weeks. The top mushroom for mental performance and neuroprotection.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="info-card">
          <div class="info-card-ico">RE</div>
          <h3>Reishi</h3>
          <p><em>Ganoderma lucidum</em> — <strong>Stress Relief & Sleep Quality.</strong> The "mushroom of immortality." Active triterpenoids modulate the HPA axis, regulating cortisol and promoting calm. Research in the <em>Journal of Ethnopharmacology</em> found it significantly improved sleep quality and reduced fatigue after 8 weeks. Also a potent immunomodulator.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="info-card">
          <div class="info-card-ico">CD</div>
          <h3>Cordyceps</h3>
          <p><em>Cordyceps militaris</em> — <strong>Energy & Athletic Performance.</strong> Increases cellular ATP production for sustained energy without caffeine jitters. A 2020 study found it improved VO2 max by 7% and time to exhaustion by 11% in trained athletes over 3 weeks. The go-to species for physical endurance.</p>
